                   , in his Dwelling house, putting him in Danger of his life, and taking from him a silk Handkerchief, value 4 s.
            </rs> the <rs id="t17240117-12-cd70" type="crimeDate">24th of December</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17240117-12-off69 t17240117-12-cd70"></join>. The Prosecutor depos'd, that he <rs id="t17240117-12-viclabel71" type="occupation">keeping a Publick House</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17240117-12-victim75 t17240117-12-viclabel71"></join>, the Prisoner came in, and said he wanted to speak a Word with him; that he replied he might speak an hundred if he pleased, and went with him into a Room, and immediately he said G - d d - n him, all the Matter was he should go along with him, and pull'd a naked Bayonet out of his Bosom, and he being in a surprise got from him, and afterwards the Prisoner took his Handkerchief out of his Pocket, and that Handkerchief was ty'd about his Neck with a loose Knot, and was then torn all to Pieces. Three Evidences, 
               <persName id="t17240117-12-person76">
                  Samuel 
                  Meredith 
               <interp inst="t17240117-12-person76" type="surname" value="Meredith"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17240117-12-person76" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
